-- SWCC Plans Three Solar-Powered Desalination Plants, Zawya Says
-- B y   R a n d a l l   H a c k l e y
-- 2012-10-04T17:06:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-04/swcc-plans-three-solar-powered-desalination-plants-zawya-says.html
Saline Water Conversion Corp. is
planning three solar-powered desalination plants in Haqel, Dhuba
and Farasan, Abdul Rahman Al-Ibrahim, governor of the Saudi
company, was cited as saying by the Zawya news agency.  Two solar-powered desalination plants currently operate in
Al-Khafji and Jubail. The desalination plant being constructed
in Ras Al-Khair on the Arabian Gulf coast would be ready within
two years, he told the Middle East business site.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Randall Hackley in London at 
